<br>
It isn't that the &quot;non PC&quot; list is lower than the PC list, it is rather that mobs will prefer PCs to NPCs if they are both aggro and in melee range, even if the NPC has higher aggro.<br>
<br>
There is also the charmed pet thing (if the aggro list is longer than 4, charmed pets are skipped over until they find a PC, even if that PC isn't in melee range).<br>
<br>
What I'm interested in is how much these techniques can be used to ramp up rapid warrior aggro generation.  I have personal experience that an enchanter can insta tash and instaslow (25% hasted) when a warrior is using charmed-pet assisted aggro on an xp mob without stealing aggro.  If the enchanter immediately sits down at this point, the mob sometimes turned on the enchanter.<br>
<br>
This is with a tank with no aggro proc weapons.<br>
